        "content": "[\n  {\n    \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/238790002\",\n    \"assets_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/238790002/assets\",\n    \"upload_url\": \"https://uploads.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/238790002/assets{?name,label}\",\n    \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases/tag/v0.86.0\",\n    \"id\": 238790002,\n    \"author\": {\n      \"login\": \"paul-gauthier\",\n      \"id\": 69695708,\n      \"node_id\": \"MDQ6VXNlcjY5Njk1NzA4\",\n      \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/69695708?v=4\",\n      \"gravatar_id\": \"\",\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"followers_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/followers\",\n      \"following_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/following{/other_user}\",\n      \"gists_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/gists{/gist_id}\",\n      \"starred_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\n      \"subscriptions_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/subscriptions\",\n      \"organizations_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/orgs\",\n      \"repos_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/repos\",\n      \"events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/events{/privacy}\",\n      \"received_events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/received_events\",\n      \"type\": \"User\",\n      \"user_view_type\": \"public\",\n      \"site_admin\": false\n    },\n    \"node_id\": \"RE_kwDOJhC06c4OO6Vy\",\n    \"tag_name\": \"v0.86.0\",\n    \"target_commitish\": \"main\",\n    \"name\": \"Aider v0.86.0\",\n    \"draft\": false,\n    \"immutable\": false,\n    \"prerelease\": false,\n    \"created_at\": \"2025-08-09T15:54:51Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-08-09T17:42:19Z\",\n    \"published_at\": \"2025-08-09T17:42:19Z\",\n    \"assets\": [\n\n    ],\n    \"tarball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/tarball/v0.86.0\",\n    \"zipball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/zipball/v0.86.0\",\n    \"body\": \"- Added support for all GPT-5 models.\\r\\n- Added support for Grok-4 via `xai/grok-4` and `openrouter/x-ai/grok-4` model names.\\r\\n- Added support for `gemini/gemini-2.5-flash-lite-preview-06-17` model, by Tamir Zahavi-Brunner.\\r\\n- `/clear` now prints “All chat history cleared.” so you know it worked, by Zexin Yuan.\\r\\n- `/undo` output now shows only the first line of each commit message, making it easier to read.\\r\\n- Added support for `openrouter/moonshotai/kimi-k2` model, by Jack Harrington.\\r\\n- Display model announcements with no-arg `/model` command.\\r\\n- Fixed an issue where new settings for an existing model didn't replace the old ones, by Andrew Grigorev.\\r\\n- Fixed analytics to support the latest PostHog SDK event-capture API.\\r\\n- Bumped dependencies to pick up latest litellm==1.75.0.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Aider wrote 88% of the code in this release.\",\n    \"reactions\": {\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/238790002/reactions\",\n      \"total_count\": 41,\n      \"+1\": 0,\n      \"-1\": 0,\n      \"laugh\": 0,\n      \"hooray\": 0,\n      \"confused\": 0,\n      \"heart\": 0,\n      \"rocket\": 40,\n      \"eyes\": 1\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/228491827\",\n    \"assets_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/228491827/assets\",\n    \"upload_url\": \"https://uploads.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/228491827/assets{?name,label}\",\n    \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases/tag/v0.85.0\",\n    \"id\": 228491827,\n    \"author\": {\n      \"login\": \"paul-gauthier\",\n      \"id\": 69695708,\n      \"node_id\": \"MDQ6VXNlcjY5Njk1NzA4\",\n      \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/69695708?v=4\",\n      \"gravatar_id\": \"\",\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"followers_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/followers\",\n      \"following_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/following{/other_user}\",\n      \"gists_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/gists{/gist_id}\",\n      \"starred_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\n      \"subscriptions_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/subscriptions\",\n      \"organizations_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/orgs\",\n      \"repos_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/repos\",\n      \"events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/events{/privacy}\",\n      \"received_events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/received_events\",\n      \"type\": \"User\",\n      \"user_view_type\": \"public\",\n      \"site_admin\": false\n    },\n    \"node_id\": \"RE_kwDOJhC06c4NnoIz\",\n    \"tag_name\": \"v0.85.0\",\n    \"target_commitish\": \"main\",\n    \"name\": \"Aider v0.85.0\",\n    \"draft\": false,\n    \"immutable\": false,\n    \"prerelease\": false,\n    \"created_at\": \"2025-06-27T23:39:48Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-06-27T23:47:09Z\",\n    \"published_at\": \"2025-06-27T23:47:09Z\",\n    \"assets\": [\n\n    ],\n    \"tarball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/tarball/v0.85.0\",\n    \"zipball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/zipball/v0.85.0\",\n    \"body\": \"#### New Models\\r\\n- Added support for new Gemini models including `gemini-2.5-pro`, `gemini-2.5-flash`, and `gemini-2.5-pro-preview-06-05` with thinking tokens support.\\r\\n- Updated model aliases: `flash` now points to `gemini-2.5-flash` and `gemini` now points to `gemini-2.5-pro`.\\r\\n- Support for Responses API models like o1-pro, o3-pro.\\r\\n- Added support for OpenAI o3-pro model across multiple providers.\\r\\n- Enhanced thinking tokens support: can now be disabled by setting to 0, and improved help text with examples.\\r\\n- Increased max tokens for Deepseek models to 65536 for better performance.\\r\\n- Updated pricing for o3.\\r\\n\\r\\n#### New Features & Enhancements\\r\\n- Added `--add-gitignore-files` flag to enable adding files listed in .gitignore to Aider's editing scope, by omarcinkonis.\\r\\n- Co-authored-by attribution is now enabled by default for commit messages.\\r\\n- Enhanced commit message generation to use system prompt prefixes, by Luke Reeves.\\r\\n- Added `--commit-language` option to specify the language for commit messages, by Kyosuke Takayama.\\r\\n- Skip expensive file tracking operations when `--skip-sanity-check-repo` is enabled for better performance, by Makar Ivashko.\\r\\n- Optimized chat history summarization performance, by jayeshthk.\\r\\n- Added custom PostHog analytics configuration options with `--analytics-posthog-host` and `--analytics-posthog-project-api-key` flags, by Vasil Markoukin.\\r\\n\\r\\n#### Repository Map\\r\\n- Added MATLAB language support for repository maps, by Matthew Tofano.\\r\\n- Added Clojure language support for repository maps, by Garrett Hopper.\\r\\n- Improved kebab-case identifier recognition in repository maps for better code analysis.\\r\\n\\r\\n#### Fixes & Small Improvements\\r\\n- Improved GitHub Copilot token handling with better validation and error messages, by Vincent Taverna and Sebastian Estrella.\\r\\n- Improved inline code rendering in Rich markdown output, by Vamsi Talupula.\\r\\n- Fixed Vertex AI model name prefixes in settings, by Wietse Venema.\\r\\n- Improved `/read-only` command to resolve literal paths correctly, by Matteo Landi.\\r\\n- Fixed encoding issues in git diff output and LLM history logging.\\r\\n- Fixed search block regex to accept optional closing tags when working with HTML content, by Mathis Beer.\\r\\n- Auto-create parent directories for chat history files to prevent startup errors, by contributor.\\r\\n- Ensure pip is available before package installation.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Aider wrote 21% of the code in this release.\\r\\n\",\n    \"reactions\": {\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/228491827/reactions\",\n      \"total_count\": 48,\n      \"+1\": 12,\n      \"-1\": 0,\n      \"laugh\": 0,\n      \"hooray\": 18,\n      \"confused\": 0,\n      \"heart\": 10,\n      \"rocket\": 6,\n      \"eyes\": 2\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/222180237\",\n    \"assets_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/222180237/assets\",\n    \"upload_url\": \"https://uploads.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/222180237/assets{?name,label}\",\n    \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases/tag/v0.84.0\",\n    \"id\": 222180237,\n    \"author\": {\n      \"login\": \"paul-gauthier\",\n      \"id\": 69695708,\n      \"node_id\": \"MDQ6VXNlcjY5Njk1NzA4\",\n      \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/69695708?v=4\",\n      \"gravatar_id\": \"\",\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"followers_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/followers\",\n      \"following_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/following{/other_user}\",\n      \"gists_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/gists{/gist_id}\",\n      \"starred_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\n      \"subscriptions_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/subscriptions\",\n      \"organizations_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/orgs\",\n      \"repos_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/repos\",\n      \"events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/events{/privacy}\",\n      \"received_events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/received_events\",\n      \"type\": \"User\",\n      \"user_view_type\": \"public\",\n      \"site_admin\": false\n    },\n    \"node_id\": \"RE_kwDOJhC06c4NPjON\",\n    \"tag_name\": \"v0.84.0\",\n    \"target_commitish\": \"main\",\n    \"name\": \"Aider v0.84.0\",\n    \"draft\": false,\n    \"immutable\": false,\n    \"prerelease\": false,\n    \"created_at\": \"2025-05-30T23:27:24Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-05-30T23:28:11Z\",\n    \"published_at\": \"2025-05-30T23:28:11Z\",\n    \"assets\": [\n\n    ],\n    \"tarball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/tarball/v0.84.0\",\n    \"zipball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/zipball/v0.84.0\",\n    \"body\": \"## Model support & provider updates\\r\\n\\r\\n- Added support for new Claude models including the Sonnet 4 and Opus 4 series (e.g., `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`,\\r\\n`claude-opus-4-20250514`) across various providers. The default `sonnet` and `opus` aliases were updated to these newer\\r\\nversions.\\r\\n- Added support for the `vertex_ai/gemini-2.5-flash-preview-05-20` model.\\r\\n- Updated default OpenRouter models during onboarding to `deepseek/deepseek-r1:free` for the free tier and\\r\\n`anthropic/claude-sonnet-4` for paid tiers.\\r\\n- Automatically refresh GitHub Copilot tokens when used as OpenAI API keys, by Lih Chen.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Core functionality improvements\\r\\n\\r\\n- Fixed an issue where files explicitly added via the command line were not correctly ignored if listed in `.gitignore`.\\r\\n- Improved automatic commit messages by providing more context during their generation, by wangboxue.\\r\\n- Fixed OpenRouter token cost calculation for improved accuracy.\\r\\n\\r\\n## Quality of life improvements\\r\\n\\r\\n- Improved OpenRouter model metadata handling by introducing a local cache, increasing reliability and performance.\\r\\n- Added shell tab completion for file path arguments (by saviour) and for `--edit-format`/`--editor-edit-format` options.\\r\\n- The `/settings` command now displays detailed metadata for active main, editor, and weak models.\\r\\n- Improved user language detection by correctly normalizing hyphenated language codes (e.g., `en-US` to `en`) and enhancing the validation of locale results.\\r\\n- Prevented aider from instructing the LLM to reply in 'C' or 'POSIX' when these are detected as the system locale.\\r\\n- Displayed a spinner with the model name when generating commit messages.\\r\\n- Bumped configargparse to 1.7.1 as 1.7 was pulled.\\r\\n\",\n    \"reactions\": {\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/222180237/reactions\",\n      \"total_count\": 29,\n      \"+1\": 20,\n      \"-1\": 0,\n      \"laugh\": 0,\n      \"hooray\": 0,\n      \"confused\": 0,\n      \"heart\": 0,\n      \"rocket\": 9,\n      \"eyes\": 0\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/217725361\",\n    \"assets_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/217725361/assets\",\n    \"upload_url\": \"https://uploads.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/217725361/assets{?name,label}\",\n    \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases/tag/v0.83.0\",\n    \"id\": 217725361,\n    \"author\": {\n      \"login\": \"paul-gauthier\",\n      \"id\": 69695708,\n      \"node_id\": \"MDQ6VXNlcjY5Njk1NzA4\",\n      \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/69695708?v=4\",\n      \"gravatar_id\": \"\",\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"followers_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/followers\",\n      \"following_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/following{/other_user}\",\n      \"gists_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/gists{/gist_id}\",\n      \"starred_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\n      \"subscriptions_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/subscriptions\",\n      \"organizations_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/orgs\",\n      \"repos_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/repos\",\n      \"events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/events{/privacy}\",\n      \"received_events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/received_events\",\n      \"type\": \"User\",\n      \"user_view_type\": \"public\",\n      \"site_admin\": false\n    },\n    \"node_id\": \"RE_kwDOJhC06c4M-jmx\",\n    \"tag_name\": \"v0.83.0\",\n    \"target_commitish\": \"main\",\n    \"name\": \"Aider v0.83.0\",\n    \"draft\": false,\n    \"immutable\": false,\n    \"prerelease\": false,\n    \"created_at\": \"2025-05-09T22:41:04Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-05-09T22:46:05Z\",\n    \"published_at\": \"2025-05-09T22:46:05Z\",\n    \"assets\": [\n\n    ],\n    \"tarball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/tarball/v0.83.0\",\n    \"zipball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/zipball/v0.83.0\",\n    \"body\": \"- Added support for `gemini-2.5-pro-preview-05-06` models.\\r\\n- Added support for `qwen3-235b` models.\\r\\n- Added repo-map support for OCaml and OCaml interface files, by Andrey Popp.\\r\\n- Added a spinner animation while waiting for the LLM to start streaming its response.\\r\\n- Updated the spinner animation to a Knight Rider style.\\r\\n- Introduced `--attribute-co-authored-by` option to add co-author trailer to commit messages, by Andrew Grigorev.\\r\\n- Updated Gemini model aliases (e.g., `gemini`, `gemini-2.5-pro`) to point to the `05-06` preview versions.\\r\\n- Marked Gemini 2.5 Pro preview models as `overeager` by default.\\r\\n- Commit message prompt specifies the user's language.\\r\\n- Updated the default weak model for Gemini 2.5 Pro models to `gemini/gemini-2.5-flash-preview-04-17`.\\r\\n- Corrected `gemini-2.5-pro-exp-03-25` model settings to reflect its lack of support for `thinking_budget`.\\r\\n- Ensured model-specific system prompt prefixes are placed on a new line before the main system prompt.\\r\\n- Added tracking of total tokens sent and received, now included in benchmark statistics.\\r\\n- Automatically fetch model parameters (context window, pricing) for OpenRouter models directly from their website, by Stefan Hladnik.\\r\\n- Enabled support for `thinking_tokens` and `reasoning_effort` parameters for OpenRouter models.\\r\\n- Improved cost calculation using `litellm.completion_cost` where available.\\r\\n- Added model settings for `openrouter/google/gemini-2.5-pro-preview-03-25`.\\r\\n- Added `--disable-playwright` flag to prevent Playwright installation prompts and usage, by Andrew Grigorev.\\r\\n- The `aider scrape` command-line tool will now use Playwright for web scraping if it is available, by Jon Keys.\\r\\n- Fixed linter command execution on Windows by adopting `oslex` for argument quoting, by Titusz Pan.\\r\\n- Improved cross-platform display of shell commands by using `oslex` for robust argument quoting, by Titusz Pan.\\r\\n- Improved `/ask` mode to instruct the LLM to elide unchanging code in its responses.\\r\\n- Ensured web scraping in the GUI also respects Playwright availability and the `--disable-playwright` flag.\\r\\n- Improved display of filenames in the prompt header using rich Text formatting.\\r\\n- Enabled `reasoning_effort` for Gemini 2.5 Flash models.\\r\\n- Added a `--shell-completions` argument to generate shell completion scripts (e.g., for bash, zsh).\\r\\n- Explicit `--attribute-author` or `--attribute-committer` flags now override the default behavior when `--attribute-co-authored-by` is used, allowing finer control over commit attribution, by Andrew Grigorev.\\r\\n- Fixed an issue where read-only status of files might not be preserved correctly by some commands (e.g. `/drop` after adding a read-only file).\\r\\n- The `aider-args` utility (or `python -m aider.args`) now defaults to printing a sample YAML configuration if no arguments are provided.\\r\\n- Displayed token count progress and the name of the file or identifier being processed during repo map updates.\\r\\n- Extended the waiting spinner to also show for non-streaming responses and further enhanced its animation with console width clipping, cursor hiding, and a more continuous appearance.\\r\\n- Dropped support for Python 3.9.\\r\\n- Aider wrote 55% of the code in this release.\\r\\n\\r\\nFull release notes:\\r\\nhttps://aider.chat/HISTORY.html\",\n    \"reactions\": {\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/217725361/reactions\",\n      \"total_count\": 37,\n      \"+1\": 0,\n      \"-1\": 0,\n      \"laugh\": 0,\n      \"hooray\": 15,\n      \"confused\": 0,\n      \"heart\": 10,\n      \"rocket\": 12,\n      \"eyes\": 0\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/212339053\",\n    \"assets_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/212339053/assets\",\n    \"upload_url\": \"https://uploads.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/212339053/assets{?name,label}\",\n    \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases/tag/v0.82.0\",\n    \"id\": 212339053,\n    \"author\": {\n      \"login\": \"paul-gauthier\",\n      \"id\": 69695708,\n      \"node_id\": \"MDQ6VXNlcjY5Njk1NzA4\",\n      \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/69695708?v=4\",\n      \"gravatar_id\": \"\",\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/paul-gauthier\",\n      \"followers_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/followers\",\n      \"following_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/following{/other_user}\",\n      \"gists_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/gists{/gist_id}\",\n      \"starred_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\n      \"subscriptions_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/subscriptions\",\n      \"organizations_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/orgs\",\n      \"repos_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/repos\",\n      \"events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/events{/privacy}\",\n      \"received_events_url\": \"https://api.github.com/users/paul-gauthier/received_events\",\n      \"type\": \"User\",\n      \"user_view_type\": \"public\",\n      \"site_admin\": false\n    },\n    \"node_id\": \"RE_kwDOJhC06c4MqAlt\",\n    \"tag_name\": \"v0.82.0\",\n    \"target_commitish\": \"main\",\n    \"name\": \"Aider v0.82.0\",\n    \"draft\": false,\n    \"immutable\": false,\n    \"prerelease\": false,\n    \"created_at\": \"2025-04-14T23:24:19Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2025-04-14T23:29:05Z\",\n    \"published_at\": \"2025-04-14T23:29:05Z\",\n    \"assets\": [\n\n    ],\n    \"tarball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/tarball/v0.82.0\",\n    \"zipball_url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/zipball/v0.82.0\",\n    \"body\": \"\\r\\n- Support for GPT 4.1, mini and nano.\\r\\n- Improved support for using architect mode with Gemini 2.5 Pro.\\r\\n- Add support for `xai/grok-3-beta`, `xai/grok-3-mini-beta`, `openrouter/x-ai/grok-3-beta`,\\r\\n`openrouter/x-ai/grok-3-mini-beta`, and `openrouter/openrouter/optimus-alpha` models.\\r\\n- Added support for `grok-3-fast-beta` and `grok-3-mini-fast-beta` models.\\r\\n- Added new `patch` edit format for OpenAI's GPT-4.1 model.\\r\\n- Added new `editor-diff`, `editor-whole`, and `editor-diff-fenced` edit formats.\\r\\n- Bugfix for automatically selecting the best edit format to use in architect mode.\\r\\n- Add alias \\\"grok3\\\" for `xai/grok-3-beta`.\\r\\n- Add alias \\\"optimus\\\" for `openrouter/openrouter/optimus-alpha`.\\r\\n- Fix URL extraction from error messages.\\r\\n- Allow adding files by full path even if a file with the same basename is already in the chat.\\r\\n- Fix quoting of values containing '#' in the sample `aider.conf.yml`.\\r\\n- Add support for Fireworks AI model 'deepseek-v3-0324', by Felix Lisczyk.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Aider wrote 92% of the code in this release.\\r\\n\\r\\n<img width=\\\"730\\\" alt=\\\"2025-04-14_16-22-29\\\" src=\\\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e4bd30b4-7fa4-4784-a10c-50315d7cbac6\\\" />\\r\\n\",\n    \"reactions\": {\n      \"url\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/Aider-AI/aider/releases/212339053/reactions\",\n      \"total_count\": 66,\n      \"+1\": 26,\n      \"-1\": 0,\n      \"laugh\": 7,\n      \"hooray\": 12,\n      \"confused\": 0,\n      \"heart\": 9,\n      \"rocket\": 9,\n      \"eyes\": 3\n    }\n  }\n]",
